Have no idea how to navigate or use this vault? Click this link to start with the RARE Vault Manual Help Guide
2025-08-31
#‚ö†Ô∏è-attention are out of the daily record sheets for the binder.  Sonja - I have printed off more binder sheets and will take to the barn this week.
#‚ö†Ô∏è-attention I brought out more poop bags. In the grey cabinet by the steps, on the bottom shelf is a bucket with Walmart grocery bags. No notices with this tag in the last week.
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Restart vitahawk 9/1
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/long-term Isn't perching but is standing. Possibly soft tissue injury? #ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Monday crew please double check the legs
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/long-term Did not see any injury, but has a limp. Was standing on one leg. Sunday crew: could you double check that you can‚Äôt appreciate any injuries either?
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term The finder had mentioned that he thought the bird had a leg injury. We couldn‚Äôt appreciate anything, but the legs were stiff. Could you please double check when you take out of cage on Sunday?
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Green pellet
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Rewrapped in fig 8 body wrap.  Recheck on 9/11
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/long-term The Ulna is starting to form a nice callus, I think when I originally wrapped the bones were not kept immobile and the healing was delayed. .
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Last day for TAB
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Metacam - 1.1mL due to the xarays and the extension on the wing.  Please refer to PT schedule.  Wrap will come off on 9/11..
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Recheck wrap on 9/4.
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Lets take a break on the Vitahawk.  Restart on 9/1/25
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Lets take a break on the Vitahawk.  Restart on 9/1/25
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/long-term Xrays showed L fx of the carpometacarpus (hand).
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Last day for meds and fluids
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/long-term Could not appreciate any differences between the L & R metacarpals.  No bruising, removed wrap.
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Sonja, please check the wings. Thank you.
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/long-term Wondering about this bird‚Äôs vision:  Turned head to look at me with far eye.  Tilted head noticeably when looking at me.  Flew close to me once, & then actually brushed against me in flight.  Wonder if its depth perception isn‚Äôt good.  Could it be partially blind?
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Likely ready to start PT in the next week or so.
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Re-check 8/28.
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Do Dex IM tomorrow.
#ü¶Öü©∫-bird-care/short-term Please document if eating.

admin/after-window-strike,-call-a-rehabb.description: Research is showing that most times birds still do need treatment for head trauma after major window strikes to avoid permanent brain and eye damage even if they perk up and fly off, so it‚Äôs best to catch them right away and call a rehabber.

admin/avian-influenza-protocols.html.title: Avian Influenza Protocols
admin/avian-influenza-protocols.html.description:
Wear face masks
Gown up when handling the birds or wear a shirt that can be washed.  
Spray gloves lightly with Rocal when finished with a bird.
Mop the floors with bleach each day.  
If you are at the barn / clinic the same day change shoes, take precautions to avoid potential cross contamination.
At the barn please take care of the educational birds first.
Use disinfectant for the barn cages.
We will NOT be changing our intake protocols; we just need to be cautious.  Please place any new admits in the quarantine area.
admin/avian-influenza-protocols.html.author: Jay

info_showOrphanNodes.description: Show nodes that are not connected to any other nodes.

info_showAttachments.description: Show attachments like images and PDFs as nodes in the graph.

info_allowGlobalGraph.description: Allow the user to view the global graph of all nodes.

info_allowExpand.description: Allow the user to pop-out the graph view to take up the whole screen

info_attractionForce.description: How much should linked nodes attract each other? This will make the graph appear more clustered.

info_linkLength.description: How long should the links between nodes be? The shorter the links the more connected nodes will cluster together.

info_repulsionForce.description: How much should nodes repel each other? This will make disconnected parts more spread out.

info_centralForce.description: How much should nodes be attracted to the center? This will make the graph appear more dense and circular.

info_edgePruning.description: Edges with a length above this threshold will not be rendered, however they will still contribute to the simulation. This can help large tangled graphs look more organised. Hovering over a node will still display these links.

info_minNodeRadius.description: How small should the smallest nodes be? The smaller a node is the less it will attract other nodes.

info_maxNodeRadius.description: How large should the largest nodes be? Nodes are sized by how many links they have. The larger a node is the more it will attract other nodes. This can be used to create a good grouping around the most important nodes.
